1
00:00:47,767 --> 00:00:50,324
I believe in America.

2
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:53,490
America has made my fortune...

3
00:00:53,666 --> 00:00:56,997
and I raised my daughter in the American fashion.

4
00:00:57,733 --> 00:01:00,563
I give her freedom, but I taught her...

5
00:01:00,733 --> 00:01:03,393
never to dishonor her family.

6
00:01:03,933 --> 00:01:07,161
She found a boyfriend. Not an Italian.

7
00:01:07,333 --> 00:01:09,458
She went to the movies with him.

8
00:01:09,633 --> 00:01:13,793
She stayed out late. I didn't protest.

9
00:01:14,500 --> 00:01:17,364
Two months ago, he took her for a drive...

10
00:01:17,533 --> 00:01:19,397
with another boyfriend.

11
00:01:20,300 --> 00:01:22,596
They made her drink whiskey...

12
00:01:23,034 --> 00:01:26,932
and then they tried to take advantage of her.

13
00:01:27,433 --> 00:01:29,525
She resisted.

14
00:01:29,700 --> 00:01:30,893
She kept her honor.

15
00:01:30,999 --> 00:01:31,693
So they beat her like an animal.

16
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:32,095
When I went to the hospital, her nose was broken...

17
00:01:32,199 --> 00:01:33,426
her jaw was shattered...

18
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:50,089
held together by wire.

19
00:01:50,301 --> 00:01:53,131
She couldn't even weep because of the pain.

20
00:01:54,967 --> 00:01:57,489
But I wept. Why did I weep?

21
00:02:01,066 --> 00:02:03,999
She was the light of my life.

22
00:02:05,401 --> 00:02:07,923
Beautiful girl.

23
00:02:10,900 --> 00:02:14,662
Now she will never be beautiful again.

24
00:02:20,467 --> 00:02:22,659
Sorry.

25
00:02:30,067 --> 00:02:34,726
I went to the police like a good American.

26
00:02:34,900 --> 00:02:37,559
These two boys were brought to trial.

27
00:02:38,500 --> 00:02:41,228
A judge sentence them to three years in prison...

28
00:02:41,401 --> 00:02:44,060
and suspend their sentence.

29
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:47,258
Suspended sentence.

30
00:02:47,533 --> 00:02:50,193
They went free that very day.

31
00:02:52,034 --> 00:02:55,432
I stood in the courtroom like a fool.

32
00:02:55,733 --> 00:02:59,426
And those two bastard, they smiled at me.

33
00:03:00,134 --> 00:03:03,463
Then I said to my wife, For justice...

34
00:03:03,767 --> 00:03:07,029
we must go to don Corleone.

35
00:03:11,134 --> 00:03:15,464
Why did you go to the police?
Why didn't you come to me first?

36
00:03:15,633 --> 00:03:17,395
What do you want of me?

37
00:03:17,567 --> 00:03:21,727
Tell me anything, but do what I beg you to do.

38
00:03:21,933 --> 00:03:24,092
What is that?

39
00:03:48,067 --> 00:03:50,532
That I cannot do.

40
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:53,257
I'll give you anything you ask.

41
00:03:56,034 --> 00:03:57,432
We've known each other many
years, but this is the first time...

42
00:03:58,834 --> 00:04:02,197
you ever came to me for counsel or for help.

43
00:04:02,634 --> 00:04:05,361
I can't remember the last time that you invited me...

44
00:04:05,533 --> 00:04:08,261
to your house for a cup of coffee...

45
00:04:08,901 --> 00:04:12,697
even though my wife is godmother to your only child.

46
00:04:12,868 --> 00:04:14,891
But let's be frank.

47
00:04:15,101 --> 00:04:17,589
You never wanted my friendship...

48
00:04:18,100 --> 00:04:21,793
and you were afraid to be in my debt.

49
00:04:21,967 --> 00:04:24,331
I didn't want to get into trouble.

50
00:04:25,168 --> 00:04:27,656
I understand.

51
00:04:28,134 --> 00:04:31,498
You found paradise in America.

52
00:04:33,467 --> 00:04:35,433
You had a good trade, made a good living.

53
00:04:35,668 --> 00:04:38,293
Police protected you, and there were courts of law.

54
00:04:38,534 --> 00:04:41,727
So you didn't need a friend like me.

55
00:04:42,668 --> 00:04:46,294
But now you come to me and you say...

56
00:04:46,501 --> 00:04:49,661
don Corleone, give me justice.

57
00:04:50,601 --> 00:04:53,465
But you don't ask with respect.

58
00:04:53,634 --> 00:04:56,260
You don't offer friendship.

59
00:04:56,435 --> 00:04:59,366
You don't even think to call me Godfather.

60
00:04:59,934 --> 00:05:01,593
Instead, you come into my house...

61
00:05:01,834 --> 00:05:03,265
on the day my daughter is to be married...

62
00:05:03,534 --> 00:05:06,932
and you ask me to do murder for money.

63
00:05:07,167 --> 00:05:09,565
I ask you for justice.

64
00:05:09,768 --> 00:05:12,598
That is not justice. Your daughter is still alive.

65
00:05:13,701 --> 00:05:18,030
They must suffer then as she suffers.

66
00:05:19,100 --> 00:05:21,965
How much shall I pay you?

67
00:05:36,135 --> 00:05:38,396
Bonier.

68
00:05:40,534 --> 00:05:44,364
What have I ever done to make you
treat me so disrespectfully?

69
00:05:45,401 --> 00:05:47,890
If you'd come to me in friendship...

70
00:05:48,168 --> 00:05:49,724
then the scum that ruined your daughter...

71
00:05:49,934 --> 00:05:52,423
would be suffering this very day.

72
00:05:53,668 --> 00:05:54,463
And if, by chance...

73
00:05:54,634 --> 00:05:56,725
an honest man like yourself should make enemies...

74
00:05:56,901 --> 00:05:59,765
then they would become my enemies.

75
00:06:01,701 --> 00:06:04,565
And then they would fear you.

76
00:06:08,135 --> 00:06:10,760
Be my friend?

77
00:06:14,334 --> 00:06:17,165
Godfather.

78
00:06:20,067 --> 00:06:22,330
Good.

79
00:06:23,368 --> 00:06:25,629
Someday, and that day may never come...

80
00:06:25,834 --> 00:06:29,096
I'll call upon you to do a service for me.

81
00:06:29,868 --> 00:06:32,800
But until that day...

82
00:06:33,735 --> 00:06:38,167
accept this justice as a gift
on my daughter's wedding day.

83
00:06:38,335 --> 00:06:39,699
Grazie, Godfather.

84
00:06:47,801 --> 00:06:51,494
Give this to Clemenza.

85
00:06:52,768 --> 00:06:54,166
I want reliable people...

86
00:06:54,335 --> 00:06:56,391
people that aren't going to be carried away.

87
00:06:56,601 --> 00:06:57,965
I mean, we're not murderers...

88
00:06:58,135 --> 00:07:01,328
in spite of what this undertaker says.

89
00:07:25,769 --> 00:07:27,359
- Where's Michael? - What? Don't worry.

90
00:07:27,534 --> 00:07:29,467
It's early. He'll be here.

91
00:07:29,669 --> 00:07:30,566
We're not taking it.

92
