151
00:13:16,736 --> 00:13:19,065
- Don...
- Michael?

152
00:13:19,269 --> 00:13:20,792
Don Corleone...

153
00:13:20,970 --> 00:13:23,528
That man over there is talking to himself.

154
00:13:24,236 --> 00:13:26,498
See that scary guy over there?

155
00:13:27,537 --> 00:13:28,933
He's a very scary guy.

156
00:13:29,102 --> 00:13:30,898
Who is he? What's his name?

157
00:13:31,103 --> 00:13:33,035
His name is Luca Brasi...

158
00:13:33,803 --> 00:13:36,530
and he helps my father out sometimes.

159
00:13:36,836 --> 00:13:40,097
Wait a minute. He's coming over here.

160
00:13:44,469 --> 00:13:46,367
You look terrific!

161
00:13:46,536 --> 00:13:48,594
My brother Tom Hagen. This is Kay Adams.

162
00:13:48,836 --> 00:13:50,927
How do you do? Nice to meet you.

163
00:13:51,336 --> 00:13:53,894
Your father's been asking for you.

164
00:13:54,137 --> 00:13:54,999
- Very nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

165
00:13:55,236 --> 00:13:56,862
I'll be there.

166
00:13:58,404 --> 00:14:01,029
If he's your brother,
why does he have a different name?

167
00:14:01,736 --> 00:14:03,327
When my brother Sonny was a kid...

168
00:14:03,570 --> 00:14:06,831
he found Tom Hagen in the street,
and he had no home.

169
00:14:07,404 --> 00:14:09,870
So my father took him in...

170
00:14:10,803 --> 00:14:13,599
and he's been with us ever since.

171
00:14:13,936 --> 00:14:16,164
He's a good lawyer.

172
00:14:16,703 --> 00:14:19,192
Not a Sicilian, but...

173
00:14:19,370 --> 00:14:21,392
I think he's gonna be consigliere.

174
00:14:21,569 --> 00:14:23,694
- What's that? - That's...

175
00:14:24,404 --> 00:14:26,029
like a counselor, an advisor.

176
00:14:26,202 --> 00:14:29,033
Very important to the family.

177
00:14:29,237 --> 00:14:31,725
You like your lasagna?

178
00:14:35,671 --> 00:14:40,535
Don Corleone, I am honored and grateful...

179
00:14:40,771 --> 00:14:44,635
that you have invited me
to your daughter's wedding...

180
00:14:49,604 --> 00:14:52,865
on the day of your daughter's wedding.

181
00:14:53,037 --> 00:14:55,799
And I hope that their first child...

182
00:14:55,971 --> 00:14:58,800
be a masculine child.

183
00:14:59,304 --> 00:15:04,703
I pledge my ever-ending loyalty.

184
00:15:06,203 --> 00:15:08,566
For your daughter's bridal purse.

185
00:15:08,736 --> 00:15:11,669
Thank you, Luca, my most valued friend.

186
00:15:11,837 --> 00:15:14,893
Don Corleone, I'm gonna leave you now...

187
00:15:15,103 --> 00:15:17,432
because I know you are busy.

188
00:15:17,603 --> 00:15:19,762
Thank you.

189
00:17:23,871 --> 00:17:26,337
Senator Cauly apologized
for not coming personally...

190
00:17:26,605 --> 00:17:28,797
but said you'd understand.

191
00:17:29,038 --> 00:17:31,368
Also some of the judges.

192
00:17:31,805 --> 00:17:33,633
They've all sent gifts.

193
00:17:36,305 --> 00:17:38,361
What is that outside?

194
00:17:46,705 --> 00:17:48,169
Johnny!

195
00:17:52,238 --> 00:17:53,794
I love you.

196
00:18:00,971 --> 00:18:03,334
Hey, Johnny, look over here!

197
00:18:04,204 --> 00:18:06,329
He came all the way from California
to come to the wedding.

198
00:18:06,538 --> 00:18:08,298
- I told you he was going to come.
- It's been two years.

199
00:18:08,504 --> 00:18:11,437
- He's probably in trouble again.
- He's a good godson.

200
00:18:15,371 --> 00:18:17,234
Sing a song.

201
